1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,958
A DAO is supposed to be the purest form of democracy: token

2
00:00:05,058 --> 00:00:11,045
holders vote on protocol decisions. But what if someone could borrow $1

3
00:00:11,145 --> 00:00:16,874
billion in tokens for 12 seconds, vote on a governance proposal that

4
00:00:16,974 --> 00:00:22,704
empties the treasury, and repay the tokens — all in one transaction?

5
00:00:22,804 --> 00:00:29,134
This isn't hypothetical. It happened to Beanstalk Farms in April 2022. $182

6
00:00:29,234 --> 00:00:33,764
million stolen through a governance flash loan attack.

7
00:00:33,866 --> 00:00:38,785
Welcome to QuantiFire. Governance is the mechanism by which

8
00:00:38,885 --> 00:00:45,251
DeFi protocols upgrade themselves, manage treasuries, and adjust parameters.

9
00:00:45,351 --> 00:00:49,249
It's also one of the largest attack surfaces in

10
00:00:49,349 --> 00:00:54,268
DeFi. Today I'll cover the major governance attack vectors:

11
00:00:54,368 --> 00:01:00,478
flash loan voting, token concentration, and malicious proposal execution.

12
00:01:03,533 --> 00:01:09,639
The Beanstalk attack: flash loan over $1 billion in stablecoins, deposit

13
00:01:09,739 --> 00:01:16,448
into Beanstalk to receive governance tokens, immediately vote on two pre-staged

14
00:01:16,548 --> 00:01:21,879
malicious proposals — one to donate all Beanstalk assets to the

15
00:01:21,979 --> 00:01:28,516
attacker's wallet. Since the attacker held majority of tokens, both proposals

16
00:01:28,616 --> 00:01:34,722
passed instantly. Protocol sent all assets to the attacker's wallet. The

17
00:01:34,822 --> 00:01:40,411
attacker repaid flash loans and kept $182 million. The fatal flaw:

18
00:01:40,511 --> 00:01:43,945
no time delay between vote and execution.

19
00:01:50,866 --> 00:01:57,143
The fix: timelock plus snapshot separation. Standard safe governance model

20
00:01:57,243 --> 00:02:03,175
— Compound Governor Bravo: proposal submitted, then 2-day voting delay

21
00:02:03,275 --> 00:02:07,828
— this prevents flash loan attacks since votes use the

22
00:02:07,928 --> 00:02:12,827
balance at the proposal block. Then a 3-day voting period.

23
00:02:12,927 --> 00:02:18,255
After passing, a 2-day timelock before execution. Total: 7 days

24
00:02:18,355 --> 00:02:23,771
minimum from proposal to execution. Flash loans are same-block —

25
00:02:23,871 --> 00:02:28,769
irrelevant to the snapshot. The 7-day delay also gives the

26
00:02:28,869 --> 00:02:34,542
community time to react to malicious proposals before they execute.

27
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:40,659
Next: Liquidation Cascades — when DeFi dominoes fall. How

28
00:02:40,759 --> 00:02:45,818
one large liquidation triggers others in a chain reaction

29
00:02:45,918 --> 00:02:51,340
that can destabilize entire protocols. Subscribe. QuantiFire.

